    "summary": "The thesis aimed at understanding the effect of both biotic and abiotic factors on Festuca ovina and its adaptation to the edaphic microhabitats, in particular, to the stress of water deficit. The study focused on a wild population of F. ovina on the Baltic Island of Öland in southern Sweden where the diploid F. ovina populations were found to carry a second copy of cytosolic phosphoglucose isomerase gene (PgiC2). This second copy, PgiC2, was originally considered as a duplication of the native PgiC1 gene, but later proved to be natural transgene of acquired horizontally from Poa species. Therefore, we questioned whether the PgiC1 and PgiC2 are adaptive in the wild population of F. ovina. The high genetic diversity within the native and transgenic Pgi loci of the grass Festuca ovina might "
